-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/platinum-market-may-see-135-000-ounces-shortfall-next-year-impala-says.html
Platinum demand may exceed supplies
by 135,000 ounces next year as the market moves into a deficit,
 Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP) â€™s Zimbabwean unit said in a report
to shareholders today.  Demand may rise to 8.27 million ounces in 2012 from 7.79
million ounces this year while supplies will probably rise to
8.14 million ounces, the company said. A 405,000 ounce palladium
deficit may widen to 570,000 ounces next year, it added. Rhodium
demand may increase 8.2 percent to 1.06 million ounces next
year, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
